headline: Restaurant Stocks Slide on Trump's New Duties
summary: Starbucks, a huge coffee importer, fell nearly 10% in morning trading, while rival Dutch Bros dropped around 8.5%.  Chipotle Mexican Grill, which imports avocados from Mexico, Colombia and other nations, declined nearly 4%.  U.S. restaurant chains tend to import equipment and packaging from China, and many buy potatoes from Canada and meat from various global sources.
